<div id="review_1902154500" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1902154500" />
    <a title="Tahera" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/9902950-tahera"><img alt="Tahera" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1605533063p2/9902950.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1902154500?book_show_action=true">Feb 03, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tahera" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tahera" href="/user/show/9902950-tahera">Tahera</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780140274233" href="/book/show/45201.A_Passage_to_India">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9902950-tahera?shelf=i-have-a-physical-copy">i-have-a-physical-copy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9902950-tahera?shelf=classics">classics</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9902950-tahera?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1902154500" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13143242451673291507">Set against the back drop of the British Raj this books explores the question of whether there could ever be a real bond of friendship and brotherhood between people belonging to two different nations, religion, culture. Although published in 1924, this book is suggestive of the mood which eventually led to the events of 1947 in the Sub Continent.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


